cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.EC, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with game theory and mechanism design, specifically in the context of auctions. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing the properties of the auction and the proof is via a joint induction, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper uses mathematical models and analysis to understand the behavior of bidders, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with auctions and pricing, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
